value.value: A synthetic analogue of the neurotransmitter gamma-aminobutyric acid with anticonvulsant activity. Although its exact mechanism of action is unknown, gabapentin appears to inhibit excitatory neuron activity. This agent also exhibits analgesic properties. (NCI04)
A regimen consisting of bleomycin, vincristine, lomustine, and dacarbazine for the treatment of melanoma.
